  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (9add73c 2022-10-23T00:09:34.410537162Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nanvil --fork-url ....\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\n`types.Sender(types.LatestSignerForChainID(big.NewInt(self.client.NetworkID())), tx)`\r\n\r\nI use this code from the go-ethereum repo to infer the send of a TX, but when the TX is sent with impersonation this code returns an error  \t`invalid transaction v, r, s values`\r\n\r\nIs this expected and if yes is there any other way to infer the sender of a TX?\r\n\r\n",
